2.01	Buzzer_(whirligig)	Buzzer (whirligig)	A buzzer , is an ancient mechanical device used for ceremonial purposes and as a toy. It is constructed by centring an object at the midpoint of a cord or thong and winding the cord while holding the ends stationary. The object is whirled by alternately pulling and releasing the tension on the cord. The whirling object makes a buzzing or humming sound, giving the device its common name.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7e/BuzzerAmericanBoy1907.jpg/300px-BuzzerAmericanBoy1907.jpg
